CEDA and odc-stac

Minimal reproducible example of using odc-stac with the CEDA STAC API. I like using uv to manage my Python dependencies:

uv venv
source .venv/bin/activate
uv pip install ipykernel odc-stac pystac-client pystac[jinja2] rasterio dask[distrubuted] bokeh rioxarray

pystac[jinja2] enables pretty-printing of pystac items.

import os

import dask.distributed
import odc.stac
import rasterio
from pystac.extensions.raster import RasterBand
from pystac_client import Client
os.environ["PYDEVD_DISABLE_FILE_VALIDATION"] = (
    "1"  # this is to silence some yelling for @gadomski
)

client = dask.distributed.Client()

ValueError: The asset must have the following fields (from the projection extension): shape, transform, and one of an epsg, wkt2, or projjson

The STAC items donâ€™t have the projection or raster extensions, so odc-stac will refuse to compute the â€œgeoboxâ€ ðŸ˜”. odc-stac pretty opinionated on what STAC items and assets should look like. Letâ€™s add those extensions.

for item in item_collection.items:
    asset = item.assets["cog"]
    #print(asset.href)
    cog = rasterio.open(asset.href)
    epsg = cog.crs.to_epsg()
    dtypes = cog.dtypes
    shape = cog.shape
    transform = list(cog.transform)

    item.ext.add("proj")
    item.ext.add("raster")

    item.ext.proj.epsg = epsg

    cog = item.assets["cog"]
    cog.ext.raster.bands = [RasterBand.create(data_type=dtype) for dtype in dtypes]
    cog.ext.proj.shape = shape
    cog.ext.proj.transform = transform
